  "text": "Swimming activity of larvae was determined with a WMicrotracker device (Designplus SRL, Buenos Aires, Argentina) as in previous works [CITATION_1] . Briefly, the activity of larvae in the 96-well microplate was recorded for 15 min at room temperature at 4, 24, 48 and 72 hpi. Swimming activity was determined as the number of interruptions of the infrared microbeam arrangement of the device. A total of eight wells per condition were measured in triplicate and results were relativized to the untreated control and reported as the percent of swimming activity for each time.",
